H0.text: What name was given to a trooper in the Parliamentarian cavalry formed by Oliver Cromwell during the English Civil War. Roundhead

H1.text: What name was given to a trooper in the Parliamentarian cavalry formed by Oliver Cromwell during the English Civil War. Steelcoat

H2.text: What name was given to a trooper in the Parliamentarian cavalry formed by Oliver Cromwell during the English Civil War. Cromwellian

H3.text: What name was given to a trooper in the Parliamentarian cavalry formed by Oliver Cromwell during the English Civil War. Ironside

A4.text: The name came from 'Old Ironsides,' one of Cromwell's nicknames.

A5.text: 'Ironsides' seems to have become the term for all cavalry in the army, regardless of their origin.
